<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-545-325  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 545 325.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Oct 22 1990 n323 p37(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Keep Bell info ban, FCC urged. (Federal Communications Commissionurged not to remove ban on Bell regional operating companies'control of the information they transport)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A group of information service companies, long distance carriersand publishers are urging US District Court Judge Harold H. Greenenot to remove restrictions on the Bell regional operatingcompanies' data services offerings.andP;  The Bell companies are barredfrom owning or controlling the information they transport underthe ATandamp;T divestiture agreement; removal of the ban would free themto offer electronic Yellow Pages and to enter the informationservices market.andP;  Briefs sent to Greene by the publishing industrygroups claim that the Bells would discriminate unfairly againstcompeting information providers, subsidizing their activities withratepayers' revenues.andP;  CompuServe Inc, the American NewspaperPublishers Association, the National Newspaper Association,Telesphere Communications Inc, and a coalition of nine electronicpublishers filed briefs supporting the Bell ban.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information ServicesCommunications Service SuppliersGovernment RegulationBell Regional Holding CompaniesUnited States. Federal Communications Commission.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>